---
name: office-agency
description: Inspect legacy agency presets. Agencies are optional presets; the default setup path generates a custom project office. Usage: {{CMD:office-agency}} [list|get <name>]
disable-model-invocation: true

$ARGUMENTS format: `[list | get <name>]`

- `list` (default if no args): show the active legacy preset and point to the generated project office
- `get <name>`: show full config for a specific legacy preset directory

Generated office files: `.ai-office/office-profile.md`, `.ai-office/pipeline.md`, `.ai-office/roles/`, `.ai-office/quality-gates.md`
Legacy presets directory: `.ai-office/agencies/`
Legacy selection file: `.ai-office/agency.json`

---

## `list` (or no args)

Read `.ai-office/office-profile.md` and `.ai-office/agency.json` when present. If `.ai-office/roles/` exists, list generated roles first. Then read `.ai-office/agencies/<name>/config.md` only for legacy preset details.

Output:
```
Active Project Office: <project_name>
Legacy preset: <name>

Generated roles:
- product
- architect
- developer
- qa
...

Pipeline: <from pipeline.md>
Quality gates: <from quality-gates.md>

To regenerate the project office: {{CMD:office-setup}} --auto --reconfigure
To inspect raw preset config: {{CMD:office-agency}} get <name>
```

If no project office is configured: "No project office configured. Run `{{CMD:office-setup}} --auto` to generate one."

---

## `get <name>`

Read all `.md` files inside `.ai-office/agencies/<name>/`. Display their contents separated by filename headings and label them as legacy preset content.

